article.headline: Jacksonville 79, S.C.-Upstate 63
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. -- Ben Smith scored 23 points and Jacksonville defeated South Carolina-Upstate 79-63, the Dolphins' 10th consecutive victory. Smith was 9-for-10 from the line and Jacksonville (13-8, 9-3 Atlantic Sun Conference) shot 57.6 percent from the floor (19-for-33) in the first half to roll to 44-28 halftime lead. The Dolphins also were 4-for-7 from beyond the arc (57.1 percent) in the first half. Jacksonville has not lost since dropping a 75-74 decision to Mercer on Jan. 2. Leading 25-18, the Dolphins went on a 9-2 run to take a 34-20 advantage on Szymon Lukasiak's layup with 5:02 left. The Dolphins pushed their lead to 40-22 on Smith's layup with 4:01 to play. S.C.-Upstate (3-18, 3-9) had 25 turnovers. Lehmon Colbert scored 12 and Travis Cohn added 10 points for Jacksonville. Pat Posey scored 18, Ryan LeGates added 17 and Carter Cook had 10 points for S.C.-Upstate.
